title: College golf: Dennis helps SLU take second at ECAC tourney
text:
A A 
ROCHESTER — St. Lawrence University senior Parker Dennis recorded a two-day total of 5-over-par as the men’s golf team took second place in the 2015 ECAC Mid-Atlantic Division III Golf Championships on Sunday at the par-72 Ravenswood Golf Course. 
Senior Jake Danforth shot a 75 on Sunday for a 154 total and a 14th-place finish. Cory Haas of St. John Fisher won the indiviudal title. 
SLU started the day tied for fourth, but leapfrogged New York Univeristy. St. John Fisher won the team title, while SUNY Potsdam placed tenth. 
■ Junior Laura Gay shot rounds of 84 and 82 to lead St. Lawrence University’s women’s golf team to a solid fourth-place finish in the 12-team Middlebury College Invitational on Middlebury’s Ralph Myhre Golf Course.
